error: failed to push some refs to 'origin' &ldquo;This means that someone else pushed a commit to the same branch you&rsquo;re pushing to, but you don&rsquo;t have that commit on your laptop yet. This can happen if it has been awhile since you ran &ldquo;git pull&rdquo; on a branch that many people contribute to, such as staging.&rdquo;
To fix this issue, run:
git pull origin &lt;your-branch&gt; git push origin &lt;your-branch&gt;
